  "prompt": "How much time does it take to get a marriage certificate in India?",
  "response": "The time to obtain a marriage certificate in India varies depending on the state and type of marriage:\n\n1. Civil Marriage (Registration):\n- Generally takes 15-30 days after application\n- Can be faster in some urban areas\n- Requires submitting necessary documents and paying a nominal fee\n\n2. Traditional Marriage Registration:\n- Usually takes 30-45 days\n- Varies by state and local municipal corporation\n- Depends on document verification process\n\n3. Factors affecting processing time:\n- State government procedures\n- Completeness of submitted documents\n- Local municipal office workload\n- Type of marriage (Hindu, Special Marriage Act, etc.)\n\n4. Required Documents:\n- Marriage registration form\n- Proof of age\n- Proof of address\n- Wedding photographs\n- Witnesses' details\n- Marriage certificate/affidavit\n\n5. Online vs. Offline Registration:\n- Online registration might be faster\n- Offline registration can take longer due to manual processing\n\nRecommended steps:\n- Check specific state regulations\n- Prepare documents in advance\n- Submit complete application\n- Follow up periodically\n\nNote: Processing times can vary, so it's best to contact local municipal authorities for precise information.",
